11.Name: rpt.4week
11.SqlCommand:
WITH MostRecentPrimaryEtiology AS (
    -- Get the most recent primary etiology for each wound
    SELECT 
        n.woundFk,
        n.value AS PrimaryEtiology,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY n.woundFk ORDER BY n.dimdatefk DESC) AS RowNum
    FROM 
        rpt.Note n
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.AttributeType atr ON n.attributeTypeFk = atr.id
    WHERE 
        atr.name = 'Primary Etiology'
),
MostRecentAssessment AS (
    -- Get the most recent assessment for each wound
    SELECT 
        a.woundFk,
        a.createdByUserName AS Provider,
        a.unitFk,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY a.woundFk ORDER BY a.date DESC) AS RowNum
    FROM 
        rpt.Assessment a
),
EarliestMeasurement AS (
    -- Get the earliest assessment with a measurement for each wound
    SELECT 
        a.woundFk,
        m.area AS InitialMeasurementArea,
        a.dimdatefk AS InitialDimDateFk,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY a.woundFk ORDER BY a.date ASC) AS RowNum
    FROM 
        rpt.Assessment a
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.Measurement m ON a.id = m.assessmentFk
),
FinalData AS (
    -- Combine the most recent primary etiology, assessment details, and initial measurement details
    SELECT 
        pe.woundFk,
        pe.PrimaryEtiology,
        ma.Provider,
        ma.unitFk,
        em.InitialMeasurementArea,
        em.InitialDimDateFk
    FROM 
        MostRecentPrimaryEtiology pe
    INNER JOIN 
        EarliestMeasurement em ON pe.woundFk = em.woundFk AND em.RowNum = 1
    LEFT JOIN 
        MostRecentAssessment ma ON pe.woundFk = ma.woundFk AND ma.RowNum = 1
    WHERE 
        pe.RowNum = 1
),
MeasurementWithRanking AS (
    -- Rank measurements based on proximity to the 4-week mark
    SELECT 
        fd.woundFk,
        fd.PrimaryEtiology,
        fd.Provider,
        u.name AS Unit,
        fd.InitialMeasurementArea,
        dd.date AS InitialDate,
        DATEADD(DAY, 28, dd.date) AS FourWeeksAdded,
        m4.area AS MeasurementWithin4Weeks,
        dd2.date AS MeasurementDate,
        ABS(DATEDIFF(DAY, DATEADD(DAY, 28, dd.date), dd2.date)) AS DateDifference,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY fd.woundFk ORDER BY ABS(DATEDIFF(DAY, DATEADD(DAY, 28, dd.date), dd2.date))) AS Rank
    FROM 
        FinalData fd
    LEFT JOIN 
        rpt.Unit u ON fd.unitFk = u.id
    LEFT JOIN 
        rpt.DimDate dd ON fd.InitialDimDateFk = dd.id
    LEFT JOIN 
        rpt.Assessment a ON fd.woundFk = a.woundFk
    LEFT JOIN 
        rpt.Measurement m4 ON a.id = m4.assessmentFk
    LEFT JOIN 
        rpt.DimDate dd2 ON m4.dimdatefk = dd2.id
    WHERE 
        ABS(DATEDIFF(DAY, DATEADD(DAY, 28, dd.date), dd2.date)) <= 7
),
WoundStateAtFourWeeks AS (
    -- Get the wound state at the 4-week mark based on MeasurementDate
    SELECT 
        mw.woundFk,
        wst.name AS FourWeekWoundStateName,  -- Wound state name from WoundStateType
        ws.startDate AS WoundStateStartDate,
        ws.endDate AS WoundStateEndDate,
        mw.MeasurementDate,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY mw.woundFk ORDER BY ws.startDatedimdatefk DESC) AS Rank
    FROM 
        MeasurementWithRanking mw
    LEFT JOIN 
        rpt.WoundState ws ON mw.woundFk = ws.woundFk
        LEFT JOIN rpt.DimDate dd_start ON ws.startDatedimdatefk = dd_start.id  -- Join DimDate for start date
        LEFT JOIN rpt.DimDate dd_end ON ws.endDatedimdatefk = dd_end.id    -- Join DimDate for end date
        AND mw.MeasurementDate >= dd_start.date  -- Compare MeasurementDate with start date
        AND (mw.MeasurementDate <= dd_end.date OR dd_end.date IS NULL)  -- Compare MeasurementDate with end date
    LEFT JOIN 
        rpt.WoundStateType wst ON ws.woundStateTypeFk = wst.id  -- Join to WoundStateType
    WHERE 
        mw.Rank = 1 -- Closest measurement to 4 weeks
)

SELECT 
    mw.woundFk,
    mw.PrimaryEtiology,
    mw.Provider,
    mw.Unit,
    mw.InitialMeasurementArea,
    mw.InitialDate,
    mw.FourWeeksAdded,
    mw.MeasurementWithin4Weeks,
    mw.MeasurementDate,
    wsfw.FourWeekWoundStateName, -- Wound state name at 4 weeks
    CASE 
        WHEN wsfw.FourWeekWoundStateName <> 'open' THEN 'healed'
        WHEN mw.MeasurementWithin4Weeks <= (0.75 * mw.InitialMeasurementArea) THEN 'TRUE' 
        ELSE 'FALSE' 
    END AS '>25'
FROM 
    MeasurementWithRanking mw
LEFT JOIN 
    WoundStateAtFourWeeks wsfw ON mw.woundFk = wsfw.woundFk AND wsfw.Rank = 1
WHERE 
    mw.Rank = 1
ORDER BY 
    mw.woundFk;

WITH MostRecentPrimaryEtiology AS (
    -- Get the most recent primary etiology for each wound
    SELECT 
        n.woundFk,
        n.value AS PrimaryEtiology,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY n.woundFk ORDER BY n.dimdatefk DESC) AS RowNum
    FROM 
        rpt.Note n
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.AttributeType atr ON n.attributeTypeFk = atr.id
    WHERE 
        atr.name = 'Primary Etiology'
),
MostRecentAssessment AS (
    -- Get the most recent assessment for each wound
    SELECT 
        a.woundFk,
        a.createdByUserName AS Provider,
        a.unitFk,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY a.woundFk ORDER BY a.date DESC) AS RowNum
    FROM 
        rpt.Assessment a
),
EarliestMeasurement AS (
    -- Get the earliest assessment with a measurement for each wound
    SELECT 
        a.woundFk,
        m.area AS InitialMeasurementArea,
        a.dimdatefk AS InitialDimDateFk,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY a.woundFk ORDER BY a.date ASC) AS RowNum
    FROM 
        rpt.Assessment a
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.Measurement m ON a.id = m.assessmentFk
),
FinalData AS (
    -- Combine the most recent primary etiology, assessment details, and initial measurement details
    SELECT 
        pe.woundFk,
        pe.PrimaryEtiology,
        ma.Provider,
        ma.unitFk,
        em.InitialMeasurementArea,
        em.InitialDimDateFk
    FROM 
        MostRecentPrimaryEtiology pe
    INNER JOIN 
        EarliestMeasurement em ON pe.woundFk = em.woundFk AND em.RowNum = 1
    LEFT JOIN 
        MostRecentAssessment ma ON pe.woundFk = ma.woundFk AND ma.RowNum = 1
    WHERE 
        pe.RowNum = 1
),
MeasurementWithRanking AS (
    -- Rank measurements based on proximity to the 4-week mark
    SELECT 
        fd.woundFk,
        fd.PrimaryEtiology,
        fd.Provider,
        u.name AS Unit,
        fd.InitialMeasurementArea,
        dd.date AS InitialDate,
